CHANGES:
- Add near top of sync/mod.rs: pub(crate) const JSONL_BUFREADER_CAPACITY: usize = 2 * 1024 * 1024; // 2MB
- Replace all three BufReader::with_capacity(2 * 1024 * 1024, file) with BufReader::with_capacity(JSONL_BUFREADER_CAPACITY, file)

WHY 2MB: JSONL files can be large (thousands of issues, each ~500 bytes). The default BufReader capacity is 8KB which would cause excessive syscalls. 2MB is a good balance — large enough to minimize I/O overhead, small enough to not waste memory on small files.

